Taco Bell, you rarely disappoint me. However, today was an unfortunate exception. I refuse to blame the servers and would rather in fact blame the poor management. The day started like any other day, I was anticipating going to Taco Bell for lunch and had been looking forward to it. "Of course! A nice treat for my partner and I" I had been thinking. Little did I know, just how sad the trip would be. The visit started as normal, my partner and I ordered our respective meals. Mine was a Nacho Fries big box, with a beef burrito and a crunchy taco, and a Baja Blast to pair with it. My girlfriend's meal was simple as well; a Crunchwrap supreme with additional guacamole, nacho fries, and a pink lemonade. We had also ordered the Nacho Fries Bell Grande, to split.  The entire time, the manager had either been wearing her mask improperly or not at all. She had been rushing the staff to hurry up with orders and had been shouting at the only two other employees present. Me and my girlfriend didn't mind waiting a few extra minutes, as long as our orders were right. We had checked our bag to make sure our orders were there but didn't discover our biggest disappointment until we got home.  The taco was missing from my big box, there was no guacamole on the Crunchwrap, and the portions were miniscule for what we were paying for (ESPECIALLY THE NACHO FRIES BELL GRANDE BOX, the portion was barely bigger than my hand especially considering their charging $3.50 for it). This was an extremely disappointing experience, considering we paid $20 to end up still hungry.  Taco Bell: do better, sweetie. Fire that manager. She shouldn't be shouting at staff and handling food if she is unwilling to be health conscious, as well as let the employees take their time making sure orders are right. My disappointment was immeasurable and my day was ruined. (i'm only half serious, i know i get what i pay for when we're talking taco bell but really fire that manager she was a danger to customers and staff)
